    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix array bounds violation in get_aggregation() function\n\n### Summary\nThe `get_aggregation()` function in the eNB scheduler was accessing aggregation tables without proper bounds checking on input parameters. When invalid `bw_index`, `cqi`, or `dci_fmt` values were passed, it could lead to out-of-bounds array access, causing unpredictable behavior including incorrect aggregation levels or segmentation faults.\n\nThis fix adds proper bounds checking to prevent invalid array accesses.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/MAC/eNB_scheduler_primitives.c`: Added bounds checking for `bw_index`, `cqi`, and `dci_fmt` parameters in `get_aggregation()` function.\n- Set default values when parameters are out of bounds to prevent undefined behavior.\n- Added appropriate error logging for debugging invalid parameter cases.\n\n### Reproduction\nUnder certain network conditions with unusual CQI reporting or configuration mismatches, the scheduler could pass invalid parameters to `get_aggregation()`, resulting in:\n- Incorrect DCI aggregation levels being selected\n- Potential segmentation faults due to out-of-bounds memory access\n- Unpredictable scheduling behavior\n\nThe issue was observed during stress testing with mixed UE capabilities and rapid channel condition changes.\n"
}